     2.1 .
Revolving Loans
     Subject to the terms and conditions set forth herein, each Lender severally agrees to make loans (each such loan, a "") to the Company from time to time on any Business Day during the Availability Period, in an aggregate amount not to exceed at any time outstanding the amount of such Lender's Commitment; that after giving effect to any Revolving Borrowing, (i) the Total Outstandings shall not exceed the Aggregate Commitments, and (ii) the aggregate Outstanding Amount of the Revolving Loans of any Lender, such Lender's Pro Rata Share of the Outstanding Amount of all L/C Obligations, such Lender's Pro Rata Share of the Outstanding Amount of all Swing Line Loans shall not exceed the amount of such Lender's Commitment. Within the limits of each Lender's Commitment, and subject to the other terms and conditions hereof, the Company may borrow under this , prepay under , and reborrow under this . Revolving Loans may be Base Rate Loans or Eurodollar Rate Loans, as further provided herein.
Revolving Loan
