Tax Matters
(a) .
Tax Returns
(i)  . The Members Representative shall prepare, or cause to be prepared, and file, or cause to be filed, all Tax returns, reports, statements or estimates ("") for the Company and any of its Subsidiaries that are not treated as a C corporation immediately prior to the Effective Time for any Pre-Closing Tax Period that ends on or prior to the Closing Date which are filed after the Closing Date. The Surviving Company shall provide the Members Representative and its accountants any information necessary for the timely preparation and filing of such Tax Returns. In addition, the Surviving Company shall reimburse the Members Representative for one-half of the cost of the preparation of such Tax Returns. The Members Representative shall provide a copy of such returns or cause a copy of such Tax Returns to be provided to Buyer no later than thirty (30) days prior to filing any such Tax Return so that Buyer can confirm that the Section 754 election certificate provided to it under Section 6.1(h) will be filed.
